description: Federal Information Processing Standards codes used nationally to numerically identify a specific county or political jurisdiction. First 2 pos = Numeric State Code, Last 3 pos = County Code
name: PROP_FIPSCD

description: Comprised of Census Tract, Census Block and Census Block Suffix.  These numbers are established by the US Department of Commerce (Bureau Of The Census)
name: PROP_CENSUSTRACT

description: Name of the Municipality where parcel is located.
name: PROP_MUNINAME

description: The "township" portion of geographical coordinates based on local surveys.  Townships typically run north or south of pre-determined "meridian" in six mile intervals. (e.g., 7, 11S, 1N, 36S)
name: PROP_TOWNSHIPCD

description: If the property is in a specific subdivision so noted on deed recordings; used for 'look ups' etc on advanced search within some counties
name: PROP_SUBDIVISION

description: The data contained in this field is based upon County and/or Local established Zoning Codes. (e.g., R, PD, R2, RM15)
name: PROP_ZONING

description: The "range" portion of geographical coordinates based on local surveys.  Ranges typically run east or west of pre-determined "meridian" in six mile intervals. (e.g., 3W, 8, 89,31E)
name: PROP_RANGE

description: The "section" portion of geographical coordinates based on local surveys.  Sections are 1 square mile and there are 36 sections within the intersection of a Range / Township. (e.g., 27, 40, 16, 11)
name: PROP_SECTION

description: Property Latitude based on 'parcel'
name: PROP_LATITUDE

description: Property Longitude based on 'parcel'
name: PROP_LONGITUDE

description: A Land Use code converted from various county Land Use codes to aid in search and extract functions. (e.g., 112, 138, 100, 102).  Please see "PROP_LANDUSE" table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions
name: PROP_LANDUSE

description: Assessor's Parcel Number in a formatted form.  Dashes and decimals are commonly used to break an APN down into logical components (e.g., 101-32-021.A)
name: PROP_APN

description: This internal sequence number is used to ensure "unique-ness" of the Assessor's Parcel Number (e.g., 10132021A seq 001)
name: PROP_APNSEQNBR

description: Absentee owner indicator code descriptions:
name: PROP_OWNEROCC

description: This field is used to indicate whether the Situs data (I.e., property location) was obtained directly from a county or local source ("S") or was derived by the owners mailing address ("M"):
name: PROP_ADDRIND

description: The Name of the property owner has been recognized as a corporation or business = Y
name: PROP_CORPIND

description: A code to indicate whether the property is residential based on individual zipcodes and values. "Y" = yes, "N" = no
name: PROP_RESCD

description: A general code used to easily recognize specific property types (e.g, Residential, Condominium, Commercial). Please see "PROP_IND" table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions

description: This field is populated with a "Y" if a Mobile Home is present on the parcel
name: PROP_MOBHOME

description: Total number of buildings on the parcel
name: PROP_NRBBLD

description: Type of building style (e.g., Colonial, Cape Code, Bungalow).  Please see "PROP_STYLE" table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions
name: PROP_STYLE

description: Type / number of stories (e.g., Split Foyer, Tri Level, 2 Story).  Please see "PROP_STORIESCD" table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions
name: PROP_STORIESCD

description: Number of stories associated with the building (e.g., 2, 1.5)
name: PROP_STORIESNBR

description: Number of Residential, Apartment or Business Units
name: PROP_APTNBR

description: Type of construction quality of building (e.g., excellent, economical) Please see "QUAL" table for code descriptions
name: PROP_QLTY

description: The primary building type (e.g., Bowling Alley, Supermarket).  Please see "PROP_BLDGCD" table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions
name: PROP_BLDGCD

description: The primary improvement type (e.g., Grain Silo, Hanger, Marina).  Please see "PROP_BLDGIMPCD" table for code descriptions
name: PROP_BLDGIMPCD

description: This represent the physical condition of the mail improvement (e.g., Good, Fair, Under Construction).  Please see "PROP_COND" table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions
name: PROP_COND

description: The primary method of construction (e.g., Steel / Glass, Concrete Block, Log).  Please see "PROP_CNSTRTYPE" table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions
name: PROP_CNSTRTYPE

description: The type and/or finish of the exterior walls (e.g., Vinyl Siding, Brick Veneer, Frame / Stone).  Please see "PROP_EXTNW" table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions.
name: PROP_EXTNW

description: The "TOTAL" (i.e., Land + Improvement) Value closest to current market value used for assessment by county or local taxing authorities.
name: PROP_VALCALC

description: The "LAND" Value closest to current market value used for assessment by county or local taxing authorities.
name: PROP_LAND_VALCALC

description: The "LAND" Value closest to current market value used for assessment by county or local taxing authorities.

description: This is the construction year of the original building. (e.g., YYYY).
name: PROP_YRBLD

description: This is the first year the building was assessed with its current components (e.g., YYYY, a building is originally constructed in 1960 and a bedroom and bath was added to the building in 1974.  The Year Built would be 1960 and the Effective Year Built would be 1974)
name: PROP_EFFYRBLD

description: View from building (e.g., Gulf, Mountains, Pool).  Please see "PROP_VIEW " table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions.
name: PROP_VIEW

description: Positive or negative aspects associated with the location of the parcel (e.g., waterfront, flood plane, airport).  Please see "PROP_LCTN_INFL" table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions.
name: PROP_LCTN_INFL

description: The linear feet across the front of the lot - facing the street.
name: PROP_FRONTFT

description: The linear feet between the front and back of the lot.
name: PROP_DEPTHFT

description: Total land mass in Acres. (4 decimal points)Example: 13000 = 1.3 Acres
name: PROP_ACRES

description: Total land mass is Square Feet.
name: PROP_LANDSQFT

description: The Building Square Footage that can most accurately be used for assessments or comparables (e.g., Living, Adjusted, Gross).
name: PROP_UNVBLDSQFT

description: The codes appearing in this field indicates the source used to populate the UNIVERSAL BUILDING SQUARE FEET field (e.g., Living, Adjusted, Gross).
name: PROP_BLDSQFTIND

description: The size of the building in Square Feet.  This field is most commonly populated as a cumulative total when a county does not differentiate between Living and Non-living areas.
name: PROP_BLDSQFT

description: This is the area of a building that is used for general living.  This is typically the area of a building that is heated or air conditioned and does not include Garage, Porch or Basement square footage.
name: PROP_LIVINGSQFT

description: Square footage of the part of the building which is level with the ground (typically the front of the building).  This is generally above the basement(s) and below the second floor.
name: PROP_GRDFLRSQFT

description: This is the square footage for the entire building.  Typically this represents all square feet under the roof.
name: PROP_GROSSSQFT

description: This is the square footage used by the county or local taxing / assessment authority to determine Improvement Value.  This figure is typically 100% of the living area, plus lower percentage of non-living area.
name: PROP_ADJGROSSSQFT

description: This is total square footage associated with Basement portion of a building.  This would include both finished and unfinished areas.
name: PROP_BSMTSQFT

description: This is the total square footage of the primary garage or parking area (i.e., commercial).  This includes both finished and unfinished areas.
name: PROP_PRKGSQ_FT

description: Total number of rooms contained in the primary building
name: PROP_RMS

description: Total number of bedroom contained in the primary building
name: PROP_BEDRMS

description: Total number of Bath Rooms in whole numbers (e.g., a home containing 2 1/2 baths would have the number 3 stored in this field as, three actual rooms have been designated for this purpose). (e.g., 200, 300, 400)
name: PROP_BATHSCALC

description: Total number of Bathrooms as provided by our data sources (e.g., 4.00, 2.50, 1.75)
name: PROP_BATHS

description: Total number of Full Baths (typically comprised of a sink, toilet, and bathtub / shower stall).  A home containing 2 1/2 baths would have the number 2 stored in this field
name: PROP_FULLBATHS

description: Total number of Half Baths (typically comprised of a sink & toilet).  A home containing 2 1/2 baths would have the number 1 stored in this field
name: PROP_HALFBATHS

description: Total number of Quarter Baths (typically comprised only of a sink, as found in many laundry rooms)
name: PROP_1QTRBATHS

description: Total number of 3 Quarter Baths (typically comprised of a sink, toilet & shower stall)
name: PROP_3QTRBATHS

description: The total number of bathroom fixtures (typically a Full Bath would have 4 fixtures - 1 = sink, 1 = toilet, 1 = bathtub, 1 = shower head)
name: PROP_BATHFIXS

description: The type of air conditioning method used to cool the building (e.g., Central, Wall Unit, Evaporative).  Please see "PROP_AC" table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions
name: PROP_AC

description: The type of basement found in the building (e.g., Finished, Half, Crawl).  Please see "PROP_BSMTF" table for code descriptions and/or click on the field name to view indivudual codes descriptions

description: This field is populated with a "Y" if a fireplace is located within the building

description: This field is populated with a "Y" if a Pool is present on the parcel
